description: From Latin immutare, immutatum, from im- (“in”) + mutare (“to change”). Compare Old French immuter. See mutable.

verbs.description: immute (third-person singular simple present immutes, present participle immuting, simple past and past participle immuted)

examples: God can immediately immute, change, corrupt, destroy, or annihilate whatsoever pleaseth His divine majesty.
